window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>PLEASE NOTE:</i></b><i> While this novella can be listened to as a standalone, it is recommended that you start with Royally on the Rocks first for the best listening experience.</i></p> <p><b><i>Lydia</i></b></p> <p><i>I’ve been asked to marry the King of Delasnia, as a political ruse for him to keep his crown.</i></p> <p><i>Being a queen is every woman’s dream… but he’s my childhood best friend I’ve been secretly in love with for decades.</i></p> <p><i>I should decline the arrangement, but I like the possibility of King Jacob kneeling before me a little too much to say no to the charade.</i></p> <p><b><i>Jacob</i></b></p> <p><i>I’m marrying the one woman I’ve always wanted, for all the wrong reasons.</i></p> <p><i>In the end, I won’t let her go. I want to keep her as my wife, my Queen… my love.</i></p> <p><i>As a king, I have a responsibility to serve my country. But I plan on serving Lydia in more ways than royal duty requires.</i></p>"; 
